  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "1.     Train outreach workers from NGOs providing services to MARPs on issues related to most at risk and especially vulnerable adolescents and ways of improving referral mechanism.\r\n2.     Train health workers, FCHVs and CMs on PMTCT and ASRH.  \r\n3.     Train PMTCT workers on delivering HIV/ASRH services for young people.\r\n4.     Conduct orientation to DACC on the need of making PMTCT services youth friendly.\r\n5.     Conduct orientation to NGOs/ CBOs on the issues pertaining to most at risk adolescents and especially vulnerable adolescents.  \r\n6.     Mobilize communities for linked response and enhance referral linkages.\r\n7.     Advocate for the provision of contraception for most at risk and especially vulnerable adolescents to prevent unintended pregnancy among HIV positive MARA and EVA.\r\n8. Conduct coordination meetings to strengthen referral."
    },
    "ne": null
  },
